
### Practice Questions:

1. Count the total number of patients in the hospital.
select count(*) as total from patients;

2. Calculate the average satisfaction score of all patients.
select avg(satisfaction) as  Avg_satisfaction from patients; 

3. Find the minimum and maximum age of patients.
select max(age) as Max_Age , min(age) as Min_Age from patients;

### Daily Challenge:

**Question:** Calculate the total number of patients admitted, total patients refused, and the average patient satisfaction across all services and weeks. Round the average satisfaction to 2 decimal places.

SELECT
    COUNT(patient_id) AS Total_Patients,
    SUM(CASE WHEN departure_date IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Total_Admitted,
    SUM(CASE WHEN departure_date IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Total_Refused,
    ROUND(AVG(satisfaction), 2) AS Avg_Satisfaction
FROM patients;

